text: thumb|right|240px|Gothenburg Cathedral thumb|right|240px|Inside the Gothenburg Cathedral Gothenburg Cathedral () is a cathedral in the town of Gothenburg in Sweden. Belonging to Gothenburg Cathedral Parish of the Church of Sweden, it serves the Diocese of Gothenburg, and was opened on Trinity Sunday, 21 May 1815. == References == ==Other websites== Category:Church of Sweden cathedrals Category:Churches in Gothenburg Category:Buildings and structures completed in the 19th century
title: Gothenburg Cathedral
